The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 BRIEFS

 Calcutta, Jan. 2: The Centre has greenlighted the setting up of 41 clusters of small-scale industries in Bengal. 

 Micro and small enterprise and textile minister Manab Mukherjee said the Centre and the state would fund the programme jointly with the industries. Work on a cluster of leather units in Santiniketan and one for surgical materials at Baruipur is on.

 Calcutta: The government will pay Rs 20,000 to the next of kin of Ganga Sagar pilgrims who die or become permanently disabled in mishaps. The accident site should be between Lot 8 a ferry ghat for the pilgrims and Ganga Sagar or Namkhana and Ganga Sagar.




